There was so much going on this day! I was super exhausted and running low on energy! I wasn’t feeling cute or in my zone! But I knew I had to put that aside and get the damn job done! There were times where I wanted to just give up and not do it. I couldn’t get the vision I had in my head for this video out on camera! I’ve learned that not all my videos will come out the way I want them to and it’s up to me to make the most out of it and still have fun doing it!  Thank you to my bestfriend for always being patient with me and keeping me inspired! @dittoengurelli  you’re the best

Ps there were soooo many people this day recording us lol 😂 it was kinda hard to focus 🧘‍♀️

node.text:
This post is for all my beautiful queens out there who are too “scared” of showing off their natural hair. Do not let the opinions of others decide how you want to wear your hair. I know there are times when you just don’t know what to do or how to style it and it can be frustrating at times. From the edges not laying to the curls not wanting to cooperate but best believe me when I say this, it’s all worth it and it’s all a journey to you understanding the relationship between you and your hair. I honestly wouldn’t want it any other way 

Representation is everything and I will forever represent for my girls all around the world 🌎 

From: one curly headed queen 👑 

To: another curly headed queen 👑
